THE Limpopo MEC for Health Dr Phophi Ramathuba says that her
department is working hard to establish how an employee got stabbed at the
premises. The man allegedly gained access to the hospital with a dangerous
weapon and stabbed his partner. She said security system from Letaba Hospital have to
explain. Ramathuba said this after the Limpopo mother of four was
allegedly stabbed 15 times by her part at Letaba Hospital where she works. According to the reports it is alleged the victim lover
walked into hospital and attacked the woman and she was assisted by her fellow
workers